<item>
            <title>[MATH-778] Dfp Dfp.multiply(int x) does not comply with the general contract FieldElement.multiply(int n)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-778</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In class &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.commons.math3.Dfp&lt;/tt&gt;,  the method &lt;tt&gt;multiply(int n)&lt;/tt&gt; is limited to &lt;tt&gt;0 &amp;lt;= n &amp;lt;= 9999&lt;/tt&gt;. This is not consistent with the general contract of &lt;tt&gt;FieldElement.multiply(int n)&lt;/tt&gt;, where there should be no limitation on the values of &lt;tt&gt;n&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12550319">MATH-778</key>
            <summary>Dfp Dfp.multiply(int x) does not comply with the general contract FieldElement.multiply(int n)</summary>
